In England, in the seven days to 25 January, there were 556,600 new confirmed cases (984.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 18 January, there were 551,687 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 1% (4,913 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 30 January is 14,023,177 (24,797.8 cases per 100,000 population).
